A few Italian studies considered a positive attitude and problem solving as functional coping styles, while avoidance strategies as negative coping styles associated with an increase of emotional distress (
 Sica et al., 2008; Foà, Tonarelli, Caricati, and Ruggeri, 2015; 
 Flesia, Fietta, Colicino, Segatto, and Monaro, 2020).
